<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>Class information items are simple <db:emphasis>name</db:emphasis>â€“<db:emphasis>value</db:emphasis> pairs that are specified using <db:link xlink:href="qobject.xml#Q_CLASSINFO">Q_CLASSINFO</db:link>() in the source code. The information can be retrieved using <db:link xlink:href="qmetaclassinfo.xml#name">name</db:link>() and <db:link xlink:href="qmetaclassinfo.xml#value">value</db:link>(). For example:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">class MyClass
{
    Q_OBJECT
    Q_CLASSINFO(&quot;author&quot;, &quot;Sabrina Schweinsteiger&quot;)
    Q_CLASSINFO(&quot;url&quot;, &quot;http://doc.moosesoft.co.uk/1.0/&quot;)

public:
    ...
};
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>This mechanism is free for you to use in your Qt applications. Qt doesn't use it for any of its classes.</db:para>
